This paper is about semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) that involves mapping natural language utterances to executable programs. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is dedicated to NLP and related topics. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as training a model to perform semantic parsing, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper deals with visual reasoning, which involves analyzing and understanding visual data, so it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Finally, the paper proposes a method for improving the accuracy of semantic parsing by generating abstract representations of examples, which could be relevant to information retrieval and search engines, suggesting a possible categorization under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
